When I was a little girl, if I was sad I’d read @chickensoupsoul books to lift my spirits. I always liked the idea of “chicken soup for the soul.” I took that idea and applied it to my life creating “chicken soup for the soul” days. I recently got to have a chicken soup for the soul day with my first acting friend (& one of my dearest friends) @briana.lane. We started with a @malibufarm lunch, a dip in the pacific (full dip for Bri, toe dip for me), incredible sunset dinner at @georgianhotelsm, giggling in robes with wine watching 27 Dresses, and a deep, deep slumber that left us sleeping in late! A true spirit lifting day, just what the doctor ordered 💕A big congratulations to Jon & @1lougriffiths on their magical jewel box of a hotel 🪄 thank you for creating such a wonderful place where Bri and I got to take a vacation from the world for a minute. 🙏🫶

Enormous shout out to this guy. There aren’t enough lucky stars in existence to count to properly appreciate what a gem of a life partner/husband/partner in crime/bestie I have in @nickcampbellna. Not only does he let me shine, he supports my dreams & aspirations 1000000%. Never jealous or controlling, always kind, supportive, & loving. Hilarious for him to wake up this morning after being my PA/extra/Starbucks runner for the weekend & say to me “I’ve never been more proud of someone in my life” followed by “I now understand our marriage better after seeing you direct.” 🤔 Hmmmm, I asked why? And he said something about how my being “bossy, ocd, & controlling” have been waiting for a moment to shine & I’ve now found a place to do all 3 at the same time where they’re needed & appreciated 🤣🤣🤣 much longer post RE the shoot coming soon, but I had to get this one out now. I love you hunny @nickcampbellna 🫶

What. A. Weekend.  

It is hard to put into words how much this past weekend means to me. It felt like a culmination of the last 22 years of my life. I LOVE acting & I love every second I get the chance to put my skills to use, whether that’s a self tape on the road or playing on a fancy, big budget TV set… acting is my love, but directing felt like I was coming home. I joked in my last post about Nick understanding our marriage better after watching me direct, but the more I think about that sentiment, the more I understand it. I want the best out of every situation & every person in my life. Sometimes that comes across as bossy (😬) but it’s always with the best intentions & love. Thankfully I've now found a new home to express these sometimes annoying skills.
An enormous THANK YOU to the always present, kind, calm, wildly talented @ellieannfenton. This is our 3rd project together as producer & our 1st as director- you're a dream collaborator. Let's keep this train moving, baby! 
Major shout out to @yougotdaved. Thanks for jumping on board when I said in early April, "I've got this idea & a window of time in May..." you can knock out a funny script like no other & I'm stoked to have the first collab under our belt. 
@claytonfarris & @vududaddy- thank you for flying out & BRING.ING.THE.FUNNY. Obsessed with you both, you're mine forever. 
@carly_christopher- from opening your stunning home to completely holding your own as an actor opposite seasoned pros, I'm in awe of your comedic ability. I know this is the first of many for us & you.
This is an incredibly long post & I had many other fabulous old friends & new friends who this weekend would not have been possible without. I am thankful for all of you coming to play & trusting me to helm the ship.
& a special shout out to my way more seasoned director friends who I called, texted, & emailed for advice. I shadowed @officialrobmorrow on THE FOSTERS, & I shadowed two blocks of my own show SECRETS OF SULPHUR SPRINGS, but nothing prepares you for jumping out of the plane! You know who you are, thank you for the advice. 
I can't wait for the next step of bringing FOUR INFLUENCERS & A FUNERAL to life. ✨✨✨

Hi friends 👋 

You know that gorgeous trail all along Lady Bird Lake/Town Lake? 

The trail that you go on runs or walks, the trail you take your out of town guests to, the trail that you view from your SUP boards and kayaks or in Nick’s case, his skull (rowing)?

Nick and I have both joined committees for @thetrailconservancy. The conservancy beautifies the trail and makes sure it’s clean for all of our sake. They do year round programming around the trail, including goats on the trail and a margarita run! 

All of their effort, of course, takes resources. The trail’s future looks incredibly bright with an arts focused approach shaping up! 

Nick & I are both thrilled to be involved in what the trail is currently and for what it will be in 15 years and beyond!

Now, how can you as an Austinite who enjoys the trail or an Austin lover who likes to frequent our city help keep the trail go, go, going? 

We have our annual fundraiser ‘Twilight on the Trail’ November 5th with tickets and tables still available- link in bio. #cocktailontoptrailonthebottom 🥳👟

Alternatively, if you have a product, service, piece of art, a great health product 👀 @ouraring, @whoop, concert tickets, @f1 tickets, a box at @moodycenteratx , @austinfc, @utaustintx, an @iheartradio hook up @tompoleman 😉, drive in movie theatre (I’m looking at you @bluestarlitedrivein), behind the scenes studio visit (I’m looking at you @rodriguez), comedy club tickets @comedymothership,private club membership or auction off a party day (👀 @highbrowlowbrowaustin), state of the art designed chicken coop ( 🐣 @thechickenapp), hotel/air b n b/vacation home that you would be happy to include in our silent or live auction, please reach out! We’d love to include everyone who loves the trail! 

We’re lucky enough to already have these incredible companies involved with Twilight on the Trail: @yeti , @alohacollection , @earlybirdcbd , @texasrowingcenter, @bubbly.bag , @campbellartadvisory, @omnibartoncreek, @andiamoatx , @yellowbirdsauce , @central.machine.works , @epicsup , @austindeep , @terryblacks_bbq, to name a few.

Let’s make this the biggest fundraising year for the trail yet!! 🫶🤘🫶

Artist planters are live on the auction site! Link in bio.

All sales go to benefit @thetrailconservancy, the main steward for the 10 mile hike/bike trail around Lady Bird Lake and the 300 acres of surrounding parkland. 

The artist planter project has been such a fun place to put my creative energy during the film industry’s strike. The idea for the planters is based off of the @artistplateproject that Nick and I support every year. I was trying to figure out a way to honor the ‘Arts and Culture’ theme of this year’s gala, celebrating the arts focused approach moving forward for the Trail, while also incorporating the Trail itself. And, voila! Gorgeous planters from Austin based artists for all to enjoy!

Big shout out to all of our artists who participated for the inaugural year:
Robert Alvarez @rf_alvarez, Arielle Austin @arielle_austin, Kel Brown @kelvy___ , Sara Carter @sara_carter_artist, McKenzie Drake @mckenziedrakeart, Gordon Fowler, Valerie Fowler @valeriefowlerart, Jacob Guzman @marsboxx, Jenn Hassin @jennhassin, Adreon Henry @adreonhenry, Elizabeth Hudson @lizmariaelliott, Sarah Kitchen @sarahkitchenart, Laura Lit @lauralitart, Beili Liu @beililiu, Lucy MacQueen @lucymacqueen_art, Gareth Maguire @gareth.maguire.official, Lauren Napolitano @peptalks, Autumn Nelson @autumnnelson_art, Zuzu Perkal @zuzubee, Patrick Quinn @plastic_quinn, Susan Scafati @susanscafati, Kelti Smith @keltismith, Tori Stell @toristell.art, John Marshall Stubbs @jmstubbs.art, Heather Sundquist @heathersundquisthall, and Tom Jean Webb @tomjeanwebb.

Now get to bidding! And if you live outside of Austin, but LOVE a planter, we’ll figure out shipping with you! 🪴
